    "body": "From: #11367 \r\n\r\n> 3\\. Don't need `lines` / `grid_lines` event at all if there will be API to get HL states. So toggle/ui-option to get only cursor updates will be very good to save rpc bandwidth\r\n\r\nAllow to listen for only for the cursor state, without ```lines/grid_lines``` events. May be ui-option like ```ext_cursor``` which will send updates for both screen line/col positions and buffer line/col positions",
